value.value: An infiltrating adenocarcinoma derived from ceruminous glands in the external auditory canal.
A serous cystic glandular epithelial neoplasm of low malignant potential. It is characterized by the presence of atypical or malignant glandular epithelial cells with an absence of stromal invasion.

A serous or mucinous cystic glandular epithelial neoplasm of low malignant potential. It is characterized by the presence of atypical or malignant glandular epithelial cells forming papillary structures with an absence of stromal invasion.
A benign, malignant, or borderline epithelial neoplasm characterized by the presence of papillary mucinous, serous, or clear cell structures and cystic structures.
